# CODEOWNERS for {{ identity.project_name }}
#
# Each line maps a path pattern to one or more owners. When a PR touches a
# matching path, GitHub automatically requests review from the listed owners.
#
# Reference: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# Default owners apply to every file unless overridden by a more specific rule below.
# Replace the placeholder below with a GitHub team or username (e.g. @your-team).
{# v2.1.5 round-3 review fix A4+B1+C1+B11:
   - A4: previously referenced a nonexistent `--copyright-holder` CLI flag;
     `/lp-update-identity` accepts it only via interactive prompt #3.
   - B1: validate the value LOOKS like a GitHub owner token (`@user` or
     `@org/team`) before emitting an owner line. A bare display name like
     "Foad Shafighi" passes the placeholder gate but fails CODEOWNERS
     parsing — emit the TODO branch instead.
   - C1: `| trim` so trailing whitespace doesn't bypass the placeholder gate.
   - B11: wrap the LaunchPad-managed owner line in clearly-named sentinels
     so a brownfield append (apply_append_only) is visually distinct from
     a user-authored `* @real-team` line; the user can delete the
     LaunchPad block if they want to take over manually. #}
{%- set _holder = (identity.copyright_holder or "")|trim -%}
{%- set _is_owner_token = _holder.startswith("@") -%}
{%- if _holder and _holder != "<copyright-holder>" and _is_owner_token %}
# --- LaunchPad-managed default owner (delete this block to take over manually) ---
* {{ _holder }}
# --- end LaunchPad-managed default owner ---
{%- else %}
# TODO: set primary owner via `/lp-update-identity` (interactive prompt #3:
# `copyright_holder`). Use the GitHub owner-token shape: `@your-username`
# or `@your-org/your-team`. Display names ("Jane Doe") are not valid
# CODEOWNERS tokens and will be ignored by GitHub.
#
# A default owner is required for GitHub branch-protection "Require code owner
# review" to work; without one, every PR routes to nobody and the rule is moot.
{%- endif %}
